	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This technical approach is very interesting. In some cases the results are spectacular (Castlevania with the C64 palette, for instance)! In other cases, it's a bit disappointing (In Metroid, Samus is completely yellow with the Apple II palette). The good thing is that the color ramps could be more accurate in terms of lightness. The downside is that some of the color replacements simply don't work. But anyway, this is very cool! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


